HEADWORD: Xanthoma
<hw>Xan*tho"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Xantho-</er>, and <er>-oma</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A
skin disease marked by the development or irregular yellowish patches
upon the skin, especially upon the eyelids; -- called also
<altname>xanthelasma</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Xanthomatous</ent>⟦br⟧
